metadata.content: # Alien Flora: A Guide

## The Singing Moss of Xylos
Found in the damp caves of Xylos, this moss emits a soft hum when approached.
- **Danger Level**: Low.
- **Uses**: Great for lullabies.
- **Note**: Do not eat. It tastes like regret.

## The Carnivorous Sun-Flower
Native to the scorched plains of Helios Prime.
- **Appearance**: Looks like a normal sunflower, but with teeth.
- **Behavior**: Tracks the sun, and also anything made of meat.
- **Advice**: Keep your distance.

## Glow-Shrooms
Common in the underdark of many planets.
- **Properties**: Bioluminescent.
- **Edibility**: Some are delicious, some will make you see time backwards. Consult a local guide.
# Ship Maintenance 101

## Engine Maintenance
The warp core is the heart of your ship. Treat it well.
- **Cleaning**: Use a microfiber cloth for the exterior. Use a plasma torch for the interior (carefully).
- **Calibration**: Re-calibrate the dilithium matrix every 5,000 light-years.

## Hull Integrity
- Inspect for micro-meteoroid impacts daily.
- Patch small holes with hull sealant.
- For large holes, call a tow truck.

## Artificial Gravity
- If gravity fails, remember: down is relative.
- Magnetic boots are mandatory in zero-G zones.
- Secure all loose objects, especially the cat.
# Space Travel Guidelines

## 1. Pre-Flight Checks
Before initiating any warp jump, ensure the following:
- **Quantum Stabilizers**: Must be at 98% efficiency or higher.
- **Life Support**: Check oxygen recycling systems.
- **Snacks**: Ensure adequate supply of freeze-dried ice cream.

## 2. Warp Jump Protocol
1. Engage the inertial dampeners.
2. Verify coordinates with the Galactic Federation Database.
3. Count down from 10 (silently, to not annoy the pilot).
4. Push the big red button.

## 3. Emergency Procedures
In case of a hull breach:
- Don your pressure suit immediately.
- Seal the affected bulkhead.
- Do not panic. Panicking uses up oxygen faster.
# Employee Benefits
## Health Insurance

Full-time employees are eligible for health insurance starting the first of the month following their start date. We offer three plans: Basic, Standard, and Premium. The company covers 80% of premiums for the Standard plan.
## Dental and Vision
Dental and vision coverage is included with all health insurance plans at no additional cost. Annual eye exams and two dental cleanings per year are fully covered.
## 401(k) Retirement Plan
Employees can contribute to the company 401(k) plan after 90 days of employment. The company matches 100% of contributions up to 4% of salary. Vesting is immediate.
## Life Insurance
Basic life insurance equal to one year's salary is provided at no cost. Additional coverage up to 5x salary can be purchased at group rates.
## Professional Development
Each employee receives $1,500 annually for professional development. This can be used for courses, certifications, conferences, or books. Unused funds do not roll over.
## Employee Assistance Program
Free confidential counseling services are available 24/7 through our EAP provider. Services include mental health support, financial counseling, and legal consultations.
## Commuter Benefits
Pre-tax commuter benefits are available for public transit and parking expenses up to IRS limits.
# Company Policies
## Work Hours
Standard work hours are 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM, Monday through Friday. Employees are expected to work 40 hours per week. Flexible scheduling is available with manager approval.
## Remote Work

Employees may work remotely up to 3 days per week after completing their 90-day probationary period. Remote work requests must be submitted through the HR portal at least 24 hours in advance. A stable internet connection and appropriate workspace are required.
## Code of Conduct

All employees are expected to maintain professional behavior at all times. This includes treating colleagues with respect, maintaining confidentiality of company information, and adhering to all workplace safety guidelines.
## Dress Code
Business casual attire is required in the office. On Fridays, casual dress is permitted. When meeting with clients, business professional attire is expected.
## Communication
Email should be checked at least twice daily. Urgent matters should be communicated via Slack or phone. Response time for non-urgent emails is 24 business hours.
## Equipment
Company laptops and equipment must be used primarily for work purposes. Personal use is permitted in moderation. All equipment must be returned upon termination of employment.
# Time Off Policies
## Paid Time Off (PTO)
New employees receive 15 days of PTO per year. After 3 years, this increases to 20 days. After 7 years, employees receive 25 days. PTO accrues monthly and can be carried over up to 5 days per year.
## Sick Leave
Employees receive 10 sick days per year. Sick leave can be used for personal illness or to care for immediate family members. A doctor's note is required for absences longer than 3 consecutive days.
## Holidays

The company observes 10 paid holidays per year: New Year's Day, Martin Luther King Jr. Day, Presidents' Day, Memorial Day, Independence Day, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day, day after Thanksgiving, Christmas Eve, and Christmas Day.
## Parental Leave
New parents receive 12 weeks of paid parental leave. This applies to birth, adoption, or foster placement. Leave must be taken within 12 months of the qualifying event.
## Bereavement
Up to 5 days of paid bereavement leave is provided for the death of an immediate family member. Up to 3 days is provided for extended family members.
## Jury Duty
Employees receive full pay during jury duty service. Please provide your jury summons to HR as soon as possible.
## Requesting Time Off
All time off requests should be submitted through the HR portal at least 2 weeks in advance when possible. Requests are approved based on business needs and team coverage.
